###########################################################################
#  diag_col_layout - a 2x3 grid of @Diag nodes tiled with the gap          #
#  operators "||" (horizontal) and "//" (vertical).  Each cell is a        #
#  small labelled @Box.  This is "column layout" inside a single @Diag,    #
#  distinct from diag_multicol (one @Diag dropped into a two-column        #
#  text galley) and diag_multi_link (a K3 link graph).                     #
#                                                                          #
#  The original brief named @ColGap, but that symbol is @Eq-internal       #
#  (defined in include/eqf) and not available to @Diag; the equivalent    #
#  tiling primitive inside @Diag is the gap operator.                      #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { diag }
@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
A two-by-three grid of small labelled boxes laid out inside one diagram:
@DP
@CentredDisplay @Diag {
   @Node { Alpha }   ||1.5c @Node { Beta }    ||1.5c @Node { Gamma }
   //1.0c
   @Node { Delta }   ||1.5c @Node { Epsilon } ||1.5c @Node { Zeta }
}
@End @Text
